    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>
                <date>23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> Dec/62</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have the pleasure to own the<lb/> receipt of your esteemed lines
                of <date>6<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date>. Inst,<lb/> and now beg to hand you herewith
                a Dft.<lb/> for $47.78 for collections &amp;c as p note annexed.<lb/> The <date>2<hi
                        rend="sup">nd</hi></date> thereof was sent to <placeName>Boston</placeName>
                on <date>15<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Inst.<lb/> for acceptance, and will no
                doubt have been<lb/> forwarded you thence ere the receipt of this.<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs. DaCosta</persName> being unwell since last year,<lb/> her copy of the
                Occident has been given up,<lb/> and is taken by <persName>Mr. M. D.
                    Osorio</persName>. <persName>Rev. Myers</persName><lb/> said ere his departure
                that he would pay<lb/> his subscription to <persName>Mr. Nathan</persName>, your
                Agent<lb/> in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>. You mention having asked me<lb/>
                lately to collect for the magazine, but that<lb/> letter must have strayed, as I did
                not notice<lb/> the request before. The Bibles and Prayer Bks.<lb/> having been sold
                you may send me a new<lb/> supply.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You will have perceived that a Minister for<lb/> our congregation
                has been advertised for. The<lb/> promptitude of the Board I believe was not
                gen<lb/>erally known by the members, but to have the<lb/> vacancy speedily filled
                would, doubtless meet<lb/> with the concurrence of a large number. In<lb/> fact the
                Bye Laws in <sic>recognising</sic> the Minister<lb/> as one of the Officers of the
                Synagogue do not<lb/> provide for his absence, and therefore it is held<lb/> that
                these laws cannot be binding on the members<lb/> while the illegality of any article
                can be proved.<lb/> But I understand that only $1200. have been<lb/> offered and
                while I know that our congregation<lb/> cannot afford a salary of $2000. as you
                suggest,<lb/> its expenses being already large, I must likewise<lb/> confess that
                less than $1500. would be very small.<lb/> I would mention privately that there is
                now<lb/> an application but of course the candidate is<lb/> not an Englishman, and
                it is not known whether<lb/> he has had much practice in English oratory.<lb/> In
                many other respects he would suit us, and</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>therefore, if this and one or two other points of<lb/> which I wrote you before, can
                be satisfactorily<lb/> understood and arranged, it is not improbable<lb/> that we
                will soon secure his services. I have<lb/>
                <sic>shewn</sic> your letter to one or two of my acquain<lb/>tances whom I know to
                be favorable to your<lb/> views; but in no community, I believe, are all<lb/> the
                members thereof found to agree on any sub<lb/>ject, and the causes which led to the
                resigna<lb/>tion of our former Minsters have therefore been<lb/> beyond the control
                of our congregation</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With regard,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I am, Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Yours, truly,</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">David M. Pizal</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P. S. I did not collect<lb/> from <persName>Mr. Simmonds</persName><lb/> as you made
                no mention of it.</p>
            <p>Rec'd for Occident from <persName>Major Wolff</persName>,</p>
            <p><persName>Messrs. J. Fidanque Jr</persName>, <persName>Sol. L. Maduro</persName>,</p>
            <p><persName>M. R. A. Correa</persName>, <persName>A. D. DeJongh, M. D.</persName></p>
            <p><persName>Osorio</persName>, &amp; self                $21.—</p>
            <p>4 D. Prayers $12 4 Bibles $10  <hi rend="underline">22</hi></p>
            <p rend="align(right)"> $43.—</p>
            <p>Dft @ 10 D/S on <persName>W. J. Haskell &amp; Co.</persName>
                <placeName>Boston</placeName> $47.78@10% dis. <hi rend="underline">43</hi></p>
        </body>
